Alex Sold 500 Units Outside of Office Depot

Meet Alex, a dad whose premature son's therapy sessions sparked a big idea.

He invented Little Gripsters, a soft, adjustable sleeve that wraps around a baby bottle so little hands can practice gripping safely.

After proving demand by selling 500 units of an early version, he refined the product and now sells on his website, Amazon, and TikTok Shop.

Mark Still Builds, Sells, and Ships From His Garage

A visual artist turned inventor, Mark reimagined a classic bottle opener after seeing a screw-and-stick version during his Peace Corps days in West Africa.

He built a wood prototype, then refined it into GrabOpener â€” an aluminum, one-handed opener that centers itself with a magnet.

A modest Indiegogo launch in 2012 snowballed after a 2013 Reddit post sent sales soaring for a week.

Today, he manufactures in the U.S. using aluminum extrusions from Utah, assembles and packages from his garage, and offers nine colors.
